  "response": "\"Designated Survivor\" is a political drama television series that aired from 2016 to 2019. Here's a brief overview:\n\nPros:\n- Interesting premise of a low-ranking cabinet member becoming president after a terrorist attack\n- Kiefer Sutherland delivers a strong performance as Tom Kirkman\n- Explores political challenges and governmental processes\n- Combines political intrigue with conspiracy thriller elements\n\nCons:\n- Some plot lines can feel unrealistic or overly dramatized\n- Pacing can be inconsistent\n- Later seasons lost some of the initial momentum after network switch\n\nThe show received generally positive reviews for its engaging storyline and Sutherland's lead performance. It was praised for its unique concept of exploring presidential succession during a national crisis. The first two seasons on ABC were particularly well-received, while the third season on Netflix was more mixed in reception.\n\nOverall, it's considered an entertaining political drama that offers an imaginative take on presidential leadership and national crisis management.\n\nNote: This is a general review based on critical consensus and audience reception. Individual opinions may vary.",
